This is `∫ ω₁, (∫ ω₂, ‖X i (ω₁) - X i (ω₂)‖^(2*m) dμ(ω₂)) dμ(ω₁)`.
For a fixed `ω₁`, we need `∫ ω₂, ‖X i (ω₁) - X i (ω₂)‖^(2*m) dμ(ω₂)`.
This is a function of `ω₁`.

We know `X i ∈ L^(2*m) μ`, so `‖X i (ω)‖^(2*m)` is integrable.
Let's use the fact that `‖X i (ω₁) - X i (ω₂)‖^(2*m)` can be bounded by a sum of terms involving `‖X i (ω₁)‖` and `‖X i (ω₂)‖`.
